El Portal first appeared as a [[census-designated place]] in the [[2010 United States census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that El Portal had a population of 372. The population density was {{convert|199.6|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of El Portal was 297 (79.8%) [[White Americans|White]], 3 (0.8%) [[African Americans|African American]], 6 (1.6%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 9 (2.4%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 1 (0.3%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 12 (3.2%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 44 (11.8%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 36 persons (9.7%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=El Portal CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0622328 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 20, 2025}}</ref>

The census reported that 356 people (95.7% of the population) lived in households, 16 (4.3%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and no one was institutionalized.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 179 households, out of which 45 (25.1%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 55 (30.7%) were married-couple households, 17 (9.5%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 53 (29.6%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 54 (30.2%) had a male householder with no partner present. 85 households (47.5%) were one person, and 19 (10.6%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 1.99.<ref name=DP1/> There were 76 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (42.5% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=El Portal CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0622328 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 20, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 63 people (16.9%) under the age of 18, 9 people (2.4%) aged 18 to 24, 155 people (41.7%) aged 25 to 44, 104 people (28.0%) aged 45 to 64, and 41 people (11.0%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 36.7{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 117.5 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 231 housing units at an average density of {{convert|123.9|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 179 (77.5%) were occupied. Of these, 51 (28.5%) were owner-occupied, and 128 (71.5%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

